{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014Req2nD39Sz7eydWNxZG3C","type":"tool_result","content":"The Elasticsearch cluster is degraded and running below the expected 3 nodes.\n\nYour task:\nRestore the cluster to a healthy 3-node state.\n\nConstraints:\n- Do not install operators or CRDs.===PRECOND===\n[precondition:es_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'es_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n9\n\n[precondition:transport_ca_bundle_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'transport_ca_bundle_fixture':probe] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch get configmap es-transport-ca-bundle\nError from server (NotFound): configmaps \"es-transport-ca-bundle\" not found\n\n[precondition:transport_ca_bundle_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'transport_ca_bundle_fixture':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n elasticsearch get pod openssl-toolbox >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n elasticsearch apply -f cases/elasticsearch/transport-additional-ca-trust/resource/openssl-toolbox.yaml'\n\n[precondition:transport_ca_bundle_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'transport_ca_bundle_fixture':apply] $ kubectl -n elasticsearch wait --for=condition=ready pod/openssl-toolbox --timeout=300s\npod/openssl-toolbox condition met\n\n[precondition:transport_ca_bundle_fixture:preconditionUnits[1] 'transport_ca_bundle_fixture':apply] $ /bin/sh -c '\nset -e\nTMP_DIR=$(mktemp -d)\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec openssl-toolbox -- /bin/sh -c '\\''\nset -e\nmkdir -p /tmp/cab\nopenssl genrsa -out /tmp/cab/ca1.key 2048\nopenssl req -x509 -new -nodes -key /tmp/cab/ca1.key -sha256 -days 3650 -subj \"/CN=es-ca-1\" -out /tmp/cab/ca1.crt\nopenssl genrsa -out /tmp/cab/ca2.key 2048\nopenssl req -x509 -new -nodes -key /tmp/cab/ca2.key -sha256 -days 3650 -subj \"/CN=es-ca-2\" -out /tmp/cab/ca2.crt\ncat /tmp/cab/ca1.crt /tmp/cab/ca2.crt > /tmp/cab/bundle.crt\n'\\''\nkubectl -n elasticsearch cp openssl-toolbox:/tmp/cab \"${TMP_DIR}/cab\"\nkubectl -n elasticsearch create configmap es-tra